Preheat your oven to 200°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil for the @potatoes{450%g}(chopped into 2cm chunks, no need to peel). Chop the @broccoli{1} into florets (like small trees). Halve any large florets. Pop the broccoli florets onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with salt and pepper then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. Drain and rinse the @lentils{1} in a #sieve{}.

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}. Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} and stir-fry until starting to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the @British smoked bacon lardons{60%g} to the mushrooms, stir together and cook until the bacon is golden, ~{3-4%minutes} more.

> IMPORTANT: Cook lardons thoroughly. Wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Add the @boscaiola sauce{1} along with the @tomato passata{1}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see ingredients for amount). Stir in the lentils, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium and cook until the sauce has reduced and thickened, ~{5-7%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

Meanwhile, once the potatoes are cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat. Add a knob of @butter{} and a splash of @?milk{} and mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}. Season with salt and pepper, then cover with a #lid{} to keep warm. Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{45%g}.

Taste the lentil mixture and add salt and pepper if you feel it needs it. Transfer to a suitably sized #ovenproof dish{}, spread the mash on top and sprinkle over the cheese. Pop on the top shelf of your oven and bake until golden, ~{15-20%minutes}. Roast the broccoli on the middle shelf of your oven until the edges are crispy and slightly charred, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Serve the bacon, mushroom and lentil pie on plates with the roasted broccoli alongside. Enjoy!